		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <span id=>Anonymous</span></a><b><span id=></span></b>
		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [2.78]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Anonymous&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;As a bard enters into thier "Chant-series" of songs ( Curtailing-30th, Flame-37th ,Frost-46th ),<br>You will begin to see an ability to "Speed-kite" a mob in the outdoors. <br><br> Lvl 30 - 37 =  selo's/Curtail/Selo's/Curtail or bellow, depending on skill (repeat till dead)<br><br> Lvl 38 - 46 =  Selo's/curtail/selo/flame/selo<br>                      ( repeat )<br><br> Lvl 46 + = Selo's/flame/selo's/frost (repeat)<br><br><br> not sure of exact dmg output, but once going, it ranks up there with druids dots, and at later levels, even better than them. At lvl 54, with just flame and frost going, its about 78 dmg every click. Now, at sometime during this all, get jboots, any mob not able to run at sow speed will feel the full wrath of all 3 songs, thats a little over 110 dmg at 54, per click. (makes HG's look like melted butter in 2 minutes)<br><br>  as a note: remember not to try this tactic in a group, the 3 dot method.. mobs will hate you more than any warrior taunt ever could, and besides, its a non-group tactic. You will be better off assisting the group than dishing out the massive dot from hell.<br><br><br> just a friendly word from a vetran.<br><br> So when that person asks "why you need jboots?"<br>well.... tell em its for entering dungeons or something... or just tell them its for "kiting" purposes. hehe<br><br><br></p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8"></td><td align="right" id="fs8" >3 Replies</td></tr></table>
