		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=247125"><span id=Scholar>Jiggidyjay</span></a><b><span id=Scholar><br>Scholar</span></b><br /><img alt="Avatar" height="73" width="100" src="/uf/Jiggidyjay/Avatar2.jpg"><br /><br /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*"/><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><br />1475 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Good [4.11]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Jiggidyjay&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>Now I know the OP posted a LONG time ago, but to clear a few things up for newer bards checking these forums...<br><br>One thing you may want to consider is that you also get Chant of disease at level 42 and chant of poison at level 50. Poison, fire, ice and disease chants all stack. Fufils will stack with those other four as well, but it does less damage, and should only be used if the mob you're kiting is particularly resistant to one of the other chants. All 5 chants have a debuff component on its respective &quot;resist&quot; (fire debuffs fire resists for example), making it easier to land the next time if the song is still up. There is NO reason you would chant kite a mob at level 54, as in his example, with only 2 chants and selos. You get a 2.5 minute duration selos at level 49, and you can do twice the damage with 4 chants (if you can handle the twist). You'll also get a DoT song later on that has a 1 minute duration, effectively letting you have 5 dots on the mob. This is all really here nor there, as by the time you have these songs, you'll probably know all this just from trial and error. <br><br>Again, I know OP posted long ago, but a few changes again...<br>our chants create VERY little aggro now. All of our songs were coded to create less aggro, as we were getting clobbered constantly. And the melee classes have changes made to them also that allow warriors to create much more aggro.</p><br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br /><a href="HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1006062" target="akztarg">Jiggidyjay</a